    Bugs
    ----

    Currently none known.

    Please send all bug reports to the @{" Author " LINK "Aut"}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Fut" "Future"
@TOC "MAIN"
    Future
    ------

    - Bugfixes (if someone finds any =8-)

    - Make it faster. It's so slooow even on a 68060/50MHz
      system. But I don't see any major improvements in the
      compression/expansion code, as these are optimized
      quite a lot. Perhaps minor speed increases when
      using different models.

    - Support for non-FPU and 68000 if anyone wants.
      OK, an A1000 with 256K RAM is a cult object, but we
      live in 1996 and a 68030 with FPU and at least 4MB RAM
      should be considered as standard. Just take a look at
      PC users (P75, 8MB RAM or more is the standard there)...

    - More compression modes. In fact, xpkDMCB could perform
      *much* better on specific files if the parameters were
      chosen appropriate.

    - As mentioned in @{" Registration " LINK "Reg"}, a modular DMC
      exploration kit is planned. That means, different models
      for different file types, many parameters to compress
      all file types as good as possible, etc.

    - Any suggestions?

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Lit" "Literature"
@TOC "MAIN"
    Literature
    ----------

    Articles concerning Dynamic Markov Compression (DMC):

    1. G. V. Cormack, R. N. S. Horspool:
        Data compression using dynamic Markov modelling,
        Computer journal, Vol. 30, No. 6, 1987

    2. T. Bell, A. Moffat:
        A note on the DMC data compression scheme,
        Computer journal, Vol. 32, No. 1, 1989


    Articles concerning Arithmetic Coding:

    3. M. Guazzo:
        A general minimum-redundancy source-coding algorithm,
        IEEE transactions on information theory,
        Vol. 26, No.1, January 1980

    4. G. G. Langdon, Jr.:
        An introduction to arithmetic coding,
        IBM journal of research and development,
        Vol. 28, No. 2, March 1984

    5. I. H. Witten, R. M. Neal, J. G. Cleary:
        Arithmetic coding for data compression,
        Communications of the ACM, Vol. 30, No. 6, June 1987

    Articles concerning Prediction by Partial Matching (PPM):

    6. J. G. Cleary, I. H. Witten:
        Data compression using adaptive coding and partial
        string matching,
        IEEE transactions on communications,
        Vol. 32, No. 4, April 1984

    7. A. Moffat:
        Implementing the PPM data compression scheme,
        IEEE transactions on communications,
        Vol. 38, No. 11, November 1990

    Articles concerning data compression in general:

    8. T. Bell, I. H. Witten, J. G. Cleary:
        Modelling for text compression,
        ACM computing surveys, Vol. 21, No. 4, December 1989

@ENDNODE

